The paper deals with coding theory and specifically with the weight distributions of cyclic codes over finite fields. It also involves the study of exponential sums and their value distributions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper also involves algebraic properties of finite fields and their elements, it could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics). The study of exponential sums and their applications to coding theory could also place the paper under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
